{
  "text": "IVIG administered 10 days or more after fever onset may contribute to reduce inflammation but are usually thought to be ineffective in preventing CAL [CITATION_1] . The rate of IVIG resistance is higher in patients treated before the fifth day of fever, though it is unclear whether a poor outcome follows the early treatment or if patients diagnosed with KD before the fifth day have a more severe form of the disease with a higher risk of cardiac lesions [CITATION_2] .",
  "citation_candidates": [
